songs.title: Tilt You Back
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I saw two faces in the light of a dead end street
Begged them for a smoke and we started to speak
Countin' bricks in the wall and my voice cracks
I said, "You see I got this boy and he don't love me back"
So we walked for a bit and Jesse grabbed me hard
He said, "Come back down to Earth from wherever you are"
But his words don't register, I'm lost in your eyes
And this dial tone will kill me by the end of the night

[Chorus]
Come on and wrap me up, let me tilt you back and swim
I want your taste on my tongue, won't you warm my bones within
Reveal yourself to me, on this dark and empty street
Oh you can feel yourself in me, swallow you down so easily

[Verse 2]
It's gettin' kind of late so I thank 'em for their time
Trip over sidewalk blocks and slurred words I know aren't even mine
And Jack's a better friend than Jesse because he puts the pain to ease
So I know I'll be alone tonight despite how much I plead

[Chorus]
Wrap me up, let me tilt you back and swim
I want your taste on my tongue, won't you warm my bones within
Reveal yourself to me, on this dark and empty street
Oh you can feel yourself in me, swallow you down so easily

[Bridge]
Half closed eyes and my shoes untied
Know I'll be falling asleep in my Levi's tonight
Jack's a lonely friend, despite what I intend
Knowing I'll be waking up to messages I couldn't send

[Chorus]
Come on and wrap me up, let me tilt you back and swim
I want your taste on my tongue, won't you warm my bones within
Reveal yourself to me, on this dark and empty street
And you can feel yourself in me, swallow you down so easily
Reveal yourself to me, on this dark and empty street
And you can feel yourself in me, swallow you down so easily
